description: In a close finish, Mystik Dan won the 150th running of the race on Saturday.
title: Mystik Dan wins the Kentucky Derby by a nose

description: Frank Stella was one of America's leading minimalist artists and a pioneer of the minimalist movement of the early 1960s. The movement challenged the idea that art was meant to be representative.
title: Renowned painter and pioneer of minimalism Frank Stella dies at 87

description: Following the mayor's claims that "outside agitators" escalated protests this week at two Manhattan campuses, city officials released data saying 134 of the 282 people arrested were not students.
title: NYC says half of those arrested at 2 pro-Palestinian campus protests were not students

description: The NCAA's all-time leading scorer played in her first professional game in the Indiana Fever's match against the Dallas Wings on Friday night. Clark's 21 points were impressive but not enough to win.
title: Caitlin Clark shines in her WNBA debut, a preseason sellout

description: Zillow Gone Wild started in 2020 as an Instagram account devoted to eccentric property listings. The show focuses on homes that defy everyday expectations in some way.
title: 'Zillow Gone Wild' brings wacky real estate listings to HGTV

description: Police said they arrested three Indian nationals in the slaying of Hardeep Singh Nijjar last June that became the center of a diplomatic spat with India.
title: Canadian police arrest 3 suspects in the slaying of a Sikh separatist leader

description: On May 4, 1970, the Ohio National Guard fired on Kent State students, killing four and wounding nine. A former student who now teaches there reflects on that day and offers lessons for protesters now.
title: She survived the 1970 Kent State shooting. Here's her message to student activists

description: What's a typical vacation activity for doctors? Work. A new study finds that most physicians do work on a typical day off. In this essay, a family doctor considers why that is and why it matters.
title: When PTO stands for 'pretend time off': Doctors struggle to take real breaks

description: Jerry Seinfeld has the become the latest in a string of public figures to blame "political correctness" for the death of comedy (among other societal ills). But what does the term actually refer to?
title: Jerry Seinfeld and the fraught history of comedians and 'political correctness'

description: Photojournalists at NPR member stations documented  protests at college and university campuses nationwide this week.
title: Photos: Campus protests continue nationwide as some turned violent

description: Weliton Menário Costa's award-winning music video showcases his research on kangaroo personality and behavior — and offers a celebration of human diversity, too.
title: 'Dance Your Ph.D.' winner on science, art, and embracing his identity

description: Wisconsin's young voters — who have turned out in big numbers in recent elections — are key for either candidate to win the state. But Biden is facing some skepticism on the state's college campuses.
title: Six months out from the election, Wisconsin students weigh voting for Biden

description: It's a popular rest stop for sea lions, but the docks at the tourist hot spot these days are unusually packed out with the slippery residents. Conservationists are buoyed by the surge in visitors.
title: A seafood bounty lures sea lions to S.F.'s Pier 39 in numbers not seen in 15 years

description: Ithaca, N.Y., will require that 50% of the money spent on its energy transition and on major infrastructure projects is directed toward those residents most at risk from climate change.
title: After adopting its own Green New Deal, a college town sets a new target

description: A flood watch remained in effect through Sunday afternoon as forecasters predicted additional rainfall Saturday night, bringing another 1 to 3 inches of water to the soaked region.
title: Houston area braces for flooding to worsen following storms

description: Cindy McCain, the American director of the U.N. World Food Program, became the most prominent official so far to declare that trapped civilians in northern Gaza had gone over the brink into famine.
title: Senior UN official says northern Gaza is now in 'full-blown famine'
